    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.24/12–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Peru</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 8, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>423. Peru Amb visited Dept Fri<note n="1" xml:id="d474fn1">December 2,
                        1049.</note> offering token payt unspecified quantity <hi rend="italic"
                        >soles</hi> as prelude to formal <gloss target="#t_LL1">L–L</gloss> sett
                    arrangement for later negot. Conversion rate not mentioned.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d474fn2">On November 14, the Government of Peru had abolished the
                        official exchange rate of 6.50 <hi rend="italic">soles</hi> to the dollar,
                        thus ending the dual system of official and free rates for the <hi
                            rend="italic">sol.</hi>
                    </note> (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 699 Dec 1) Amb informed offer
                    appreciated but Dept unable consider any <hi rend="italic">soles</hi> payt not
                    covered by formal sett specifying over-all terms of payt and exch rate. No
                    conclusion reached. Dept agreed to furnish Amb this week draft sett formula
                    which it believes would be acceptable to Dept. Further info airmail.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d474fn3">See instruction No. 310, December 28, to Lima, <ref
                            target="#pg_775">p. 775</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
